docs.abstract: In an interview, one of the leading candidates for the 2020 Democratic presidential nomination discusses his long-held opposition to war and his support for socialist leaders.
docs.snippet: In an interview, one of the leading candidates for the 2020 Democratic presidential nomination discusses his long-held opposition to war and his support for socialist leaders.
docs.lead_paragraph: As Burlington’s mayor from 1981 to 1989, Bernie Sanders tried to infuse local politics with international issues. From his earliest days in office, Mr. Sanders aimed to execute his own foreign policy, repudiating President Ronald Reagan’s aggressive support for anti-communist governments and resistance forces, while going further than many Democrats in backing socialist leaders.

headline.main: ‘I Did My Best to Stop American Foreign Policy’: Bernie Sanders on the 1980s
headline.print_headline: Sanders Defends Views On U.S. Foreign Policy: ‘I Make No Apologies’

docs.abstract: While some of the 2020 Democrats have sworn off big donors, Joe Biden and his campaign have welcomed them into the fold.
docs.snippet: While some of the 2020 Democrats have sworn off big donors, Joe Biden and his campaign have welcomed them into the fold.
docs.lead_paragraph: A couple of days before Joseph R. Biden Jr. announced his campaign for president, he spent 45 minutes on the phone with John Morgan, a major Florida political donor. As they chatted, Mr. Morgan suggested that the former vice president would be jealous to know that he was lounging poolside, a cigar in hand, with his two German shepherds by his side.

headline.main: As Biden Rakes In Big Money, Will There Be a Political Cost?
headline.print_headline: Biden Embraces Big Donors as Rivals Give Them the Cold Shoulder

docs.abstract: The Washington governor has long been a leading voice on climate change. He believes he will gain prominence as more voters learn of his record and proposals.
docs.snippet: The Washington governor has long been a leading voice on climate change. He believes he will gain prominence as more voters learn of his record and proposals.
docs.lead_paragraph: RAYMOND, N.H. — For years, climate change was an issue of passionate concern to a few voters, but never enough to ripple presidential politics. The Hillary Clinton-Donald Trump debates in 2016 notoriously did not include any questions from moderators about global warming.

headline.main: Climate Change Is Catching On With Voters. Why Isn’t Jay Inslee?
headline.print_headline: Issue of Climate Change Rushes to Stage Center; Candidate Is in the Wings
